OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFamily struggles with cost 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fof cancer treatment        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A woman whose four-year-old son has    
OL,6, cancer says she worries about keeping a
OL,7, roof above her family's head.          
OL,9,FNatalie Ridler, 33, from Swansea, said 
OL,10,Fthe cost of travelling for treatment   
OL,11,Fwhile not being able to work as much   
OL,12,Fhas led to sleepless nights.           
OL,14,FShe set up a charity in son Morgan's   
OL,15,Fname to bridge gaps in support.        
OL,17,FThe Wales Cancer Alliance said it is a 
OL,18,F"balancing act" for charities as they  
OL,19,Fface fewer donations whilst demand     
OL,20,Fcontinues to grow.                     
